  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with a central bank account, you typically need to follow specific procedures set by the bank. Here are the general steps you might take:\n\n1. **Visit the Bank Branch**: The most reliable way is to visit the branch where you hold your account. Bring valid identification (such as your national ID, passport, or any other identification required by the bank).\n\n2. **Fill Out the Form**: Ask the bank officials for the necessary form to update your mobile number. Fill it out as required.\n\n3. **Provide Documentation**: You may need to provide some documentation, such as proof of identity and possibly proof of address, depending on the bank\u2019s policies.\n\n4. **Verification Process**: The bank may have a verification process to confirm your identity before updating the mobile number.\n\n5. **Receive Confirmation**: Once your mobile number is successfully registered, ensure you receive confirmation, such as a receipt or a notification.\n\n6. **Online Option**: Check if the bank offers an online option to update your mobile number through their website or mobile banking app. This may require you to log in to your account and follow specific prompts.\n\n7. **Customer Service**: If you're unable to visit a branch, contact the bank\u2019s customer service via phone or email and inquire about the procedure to update your mobile number.\n\nRemember to check the specific requirements and procedures of your central bank, as they may vary.",
